        <legis-type>A BILL</legis-type>
        <official-title>To prohibit the National Education Association from engaging in lobbying
            activities.</official-title>
    </form>
    <legis-body>
        <section id="S1" section-type="section-one">
            <enum>1.</enum>
            <header>Short title</header>
 <text display-inline="no-display-inline">This Act may be cited as the <quote><short-title>Terminating Education Association Congressional Handouts Act</short-title></quote> or the <quote><short-title>TEACH Act</short-title></quote>.</text>
        </section>
        <section commented="no" display-inline="no-display-inline" id="idf5ddd2045d2d4841b3ee6aa4ed9927a9">
            <enum>2.</enum>
            <header>Prohibition on NEA lobbying</header>
            <subsection commented="no" display-inline="no-display-inline"
                id="id0cdaa6209f564bafacda61071d3d0295">
                <enum>(a)</enum>
                <header display-inline="yes-display-inline">In General</header>
 <text display-inline="yes-display-inline"><external-xref legal-doc="usc-chapter" parsable-cite="usc-chapter/36/1511">Chapter 1511</external-xref> of title 36, United States Code, is amended by adding at the end the following new section:</text>
                <quoted-block style="USC" display-inline="no-display-inline"
                    id="id412bdd232aa646fab56ac75b6cf44b55">
                    <section commented="no" display-inline="no-display-inline"
                        section-type="subsequent-section" id="id6357825600f244488ffca3bada7fb01f">
                        <enum>151109.</enum>
                        <header>Prohibition on lobbying</header>
                        <subsection id="idfd3969f0d12a4c288e3cdb206560e325">
                            <enum>(a)</enum>
                            <header>In General</header>
 <text>The corporation shall not engage in lobbying activities (as defined in section 3 of the Lobbying Disclosure Act of 1995 (<external-xref legal-doc="usc" parsable-cite="usc/2/1602">2 U.S.C. 1602</external-xref>)).</text>
                        </subsection>
                        <subsection commented="no" display-inline="no-display-inline"
                            id="idde0c0af8c719474f9ac146b3d6480134">
                            <enum>(b)</enum>
                            <header>Annual certification; maintenance of records</header>
 <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">The corporation shall submit an annual certification to the Secretary of Education containing an assurance that the corporation has not engaged in any such lobbying activities. The corporation shall maintain such records as the Secretary of Education may require to facilitate an effective audit of the certification.</text>
                        </subsection>
                        <subsection commented="no" display-inline="no-display-inline"
                            id="id8291d853e06649b198d3e2132a9f8116">
                            <enum>(c)</enum>
                            <header>Penalty</header>
 <text>The penalty for a violation of the prohibition under subsection (a) shall be termination of the status of the corporation as a federally chartered corporation.</text>
                        </subsection>
                    </section>
                    <after-quoted-block>.</after-quoted-block>
                </quoted-block>
            </subsection>
            <subsection id="idfe8d0979bee84f8cb825b52f16543f58">
                <enum>(b)</enum>
                <header>Clerical amendment</header>
 <text>The table of sections for <external-xref legal-doc="usc-chapter" parsable-cite="usc-chapter/36/1511">chapter 1511</external-xref> of title 36, United States Code, is amended by adding after the item relating to section 151108 the following:</text>
                <quoted-block style="USC" id="idccb17686-a0b1-4a36-b45c-8d5e4fdc6338">
                    <toc>
                        <toc-entry level="section">151109. Prohibition on lobbying. </toc-entry>
                    </toc>
                    <after-quoted-block>.</after-quoted-block>
                </quoted-block>
            </subsection>
        </section>
